Similar synergy has been shown between Ag and TiO2. Ag enhances photocatalysis by enhancing charge separation at the surface of the TiO2 (Sökmen et al. 2001; He et al. 2002; Hirakawa and Kamat 2005; Kubacka et al. 2008b; Liu et al. 2007b; Musil et al. 2009). Ag+ is antimicrobial and can also enhance generation of ROS (Eqs. 12, 13 and 14).
